1
00:00:01,106 --> 00:00:02,649
[♪ upbeat music plays]

2
00:00:30,427 --> 00:00:34,056
DOCTOR ON THE EDGE

3
00:00:44,149 --> 00:00:46,902
THIS IS A WORK OF FICTION
SOME SCENES WERE GENERATED USING AI

4
00:00:46,985 --> 00:00:49,071
CHILD ACTORS AND ANIMALS
WERE FILMED SAFELY

5
00:00:49,154 --> 00:00:50,364
[♪ marching music plays]

6
00:00:50,447 --> 00:00:53,241
THE CRADLE OF ELITE SOLDIERS

7
00:00:57,704 --> 00:00:59,623
-Company, attention!
-[soldiers] Attention!

8
00:01:00,832 --> 00:01:04,586
[officer 1] I don't care what kind of
people you were outside.

9
00:01:05,379 --> 00:01:09,508
The only thing I'm interested in
is making true soldiers out of you,

10
00:01:10,092 --> 00:01:12,928
so make sure to give it your all
in training. Understood?

11
00:01:13,011 --> 00:01:14,471
[soldiers] Understood, sir!

12
00:01:14,554 --> 00:01:16,640
That was pathetic!
Everyone, down on the ground!

13
00:01:17,391 --> 00:01:19,184
[soldiers] Down on the ground!

14
00:01:20,977 --> 00:01:23,980
[officer 1] On one, "I will."
On two, "Chant louder."

15
00:01:24,064 --> 00:01:25,941
-One!
-[soldiers] I will!

16
00:01:26,024 --> 00:01:27,025
-[officer 1] Two!
-Chant louder!

17
00:01:27,109 --> 00:01:28,694
[officer 1] Is that the best you can do?

18
00:01:28,777 --> 00:01:30,487
-One!
-[soldiers] I will!

19
00:01:30,570 --> 00:01:32,155
-Two!
-Chant louder!

20
00:01:32,239 --> 00:01:33,448
-One!
-I will!

21
00:01:33,532 --> 00:01:34,908
-Two!
-Chant louder!

22
00:01:34,991 --> 00:01:36,535
-One!
-I will!

23
00:01:36,618 --> 00:01:40,288
[narrator] Korean men have a duty
to serve in the military.

24
00:01:40,372 --> 00:01:41,373
[soldiers] Chant louder!

25
00:01:48,296 --> 00:01:50,632
[officer 2] What do you think
you're doing, putting on makeup?

26
00:01:50,715 --> 00:01:52,092
All troops, on your feet!

27
00:01:53,677 --> 00:01:55,595
To the signpost and back!

28
00:01:55,679 --> 00:01:57,097
Run!

29
00:01:58,807 --> 00:02:00,267
[officer 3] Faster!

30
00:02:01,143 --> 00:02:02,936
[narrator] Our Creed.

31
00:02:04,187 --> 00:02:06,648
One. We defend liberal democracy

32
00:02:06,731 --> 00:02:08,150
and help reunify the nation.

33
00:02:12,863 --> 00:02:18,326
Two. We train as if in real combat
and become victors in ground warfare.

34
00:02:18,410 --> 00:02:19,411
[soldiers] One!

35
00:02:20,412 --> 00:02:21,413
Two!

36
00:02:21,913 --> 00:02:23,540
-[soldiers] Three!
-[grunts]

37
00:02:23,623 --> 00:02:24,791
[soldiers] Four!

38
00:02:25,459 --> 00:02:27,294
[groans] What the heck?

39
00:02:29,004 --> 00:02:30,714
Sir, it's a rock!

40
00:02:30,797 --> 00:02:33,133
No kidding, you idiot.
Of course it's a rock.

41
00:02:33,216 --> 00:02:36,136
-I think I sprained my back. Help!
-[soldier 1] Come on, be quiet.

42
00:02:36,219 --> 00:02:37,846
-Help!
-[soldier 2] Hey, man. Be quiet!

43
00:02:37,929 --> 00:02:38,930
-Why am I!
-[officer 3] Two!

44
00:02:39,014 --> 00:02:40,015
Like this?

45
00:02:40,098 --> 00:02:41,600
-[officer 3] One!
-Why am I!

46
00:02:41,683 --> 00:02:43,101
-Two!
-Like this?

47
00:02:43,185 --> 00:02:44,561
-[officer 3] One!
-Why am I!

48
00:02:44,644 --> 00:02:46,188
-[officer 3] Two!
-Like this?

49
00:02:46,271 --> 00:02:48,440
-[officer 3] We!
-Can do it!

50
00:02:48,523 --> 00:02:50,525
-We!
-Can do it!

51
00:02:50,609 --> 00:02:52,027
-Left foot!
-[person 1] Three.

52
00:02:52,736 --> 00:02:54,654
-[officer 3] Left foot!
-[narrator] We obey regulations…

53
00:02:54,738 --> 00:02:56,198
[officer 3] Thirty seconds left to eat!

54
00:02:56,281 --> 00:02:58,033
…and follow the orders of our superiors.

55
00:02:58,116 --> 00:03:00,202
[officer 3] Anyone leaving leftovers
will regret it. Got it?

56
00:03:00,285 --> 00:03:01,369
[soldiers] Yes, sir!

57
00:03:07,292 --> 00:03:09,628
I can… [groans, panting]

58
00:03:11,129 --> 00:03:12,380
…do it!

59
00:03:12,964 --> 00:03:15,884
I can… [strains]

60
00:03:19,012 --> 00:03:20,013
Sir!

61
00:03:20,847 --> 00:03:22,974
Please… help me!

62
00:03:23,058 --> 00:03:25,727
It'll take more than that
to save our nation!

63
00:03:28,063 --> 00:03:29,648
[panting]

64
00:03:31,816 --> 00:03:35,028
[narrator] I can't save it because…

65
00:03:36,571 --> 00:03:37,906
I'm not a soldier.

66
00:03:38,698 --> 00:03:41,201
[♪ marching music plays]

67
00:03:41,284 --> 00:03:43,161
ASSISTANT INSTRUCTOR

68
00:03:43,245 --> 00:03:46,873
CONFIDENCE WALL
INCLINED WALL SCALING

69
00:03:53,255 --> 00:03:54,339
Oh.

70
00:03:54,422 --> 00:03:56,132
-[both grunting]
-[soldiers exclaim]

71
00:03:56,216 --> 00:03:57,926
-[bone snaps]
-[soldiers gasp]

72
00:03:58,009 --> 00:04:00,887
-Hey! Don't we have a medic here?
-[assistant instructor groaning]

73
00:04:03,390 --> 00:04:04,516
[assistant 1] Move!

74
00:04:05,100 --> 00:04:06,226
Hey, push!

75
00:04:07,310 --> 00:04:09,062
Wait! You shouldn't move him like that.

76
00:04:09,145 --> 00:04:10,939
[assistant instructor groaning]
STYLE
::cue()

77
00:04:14,693 --> 00:04:17,153
[breathes heavily] It's a fracture.
Any orthopedic surgeons?

78
00:04:17,237 --> 00:04:18,863
[stutters] I'm an orthopedic surgeon.

79
00:04:20,532 --> 00:04:21,825
-Please take a look.
-Okay.

80
00:04:21,908 --> 00:04:24,661
[orthopedic surgeon]
Sir, I'm going to apply pressure here.

81
00:04:24,744 --> 00:04:27,205
-Can you feel anything?
-How's the patient?

82
00:04:27,289 --> 00:04:29,875
[soldier 1] No fractures,
but the laceration is deep.

83
00:04:29,958 --> 00:04:32,544
We need to irrigate and suture it
before it gets infected.

84
00:04:33,920 --> 00:04:36,006
Do we have any alcohol
and saline solution?

85
00:04:40,594 --> 00:04:42,721
Don't scrunch your face,
or the wound might open.

86
00:04:42,804 --> 00:04:43,805
Please hang in there.

87
00:04:43,889 --> 00:04:45,849
Hand me the saline solution. Hurry.

88
00:04:45,932 --> 00:04:47,726
Hold down his hands, please.

89
00:04:53,690 --> 00:04:56,902
[narrator] I'm a public health doctor
who's to serve a three-year term

90
00:04:57,652 --> 00:05:03,158
in medically underserved areas
in lieu of regular military service.

91
00:05:03,241 --> 00:05:05,535
PUBLIC HEALTH DOCTOR

92
00:05:07,495 --> 00:05:09,080
It's a closed fracture in the left arm.

93
00:05:09,164 --> 00:05:10,582
Okay.

94
00:05:10,665 --> 00:05:14,628
-Can you feel anything in your fingertips?
-No, I can't. [groans]

95
00:05:14,711 --> 00:05:18,214
Sir, would you mind
if I sutured this laceration?

96
00:05:18,298 --> 00:05:20,592
Uh. Would you do that for me?

97
00:05:25,597 --> 00:05:26,598
[patient] Wait.

98
00:05:26,681 --> 00:05:27,682
Yes?

99
00:05:28,558 --> 00:05:30,393
Would this leave a scar on my face?

100
00:05:31,269 --> 00:05:32,854
I'm an aspiring actor.

101
00:05:33,647 --> 00:05:34,898
If I got a scar on my face…

102
00:05:35,482 --> 00:05:37,150
You don't have to worry about that.

103
00:05:37,233 --> 00:05:39,819
He's a board-certified plastic surgeon
at a university hospital.

104
00:05:39,903 --> 00:05:41,321
He'll make sure there's no scar.

105
00:05:41,404 --> 00:05:43,031
[sighs]

106
00:05:43,114 --> 00:05:44,908
-Thank you.
-Sure.

107
00:05:45,825 --> 00:05:47,744
-Please turn your head a little.
-Okay.

108
00:05:54,626 --> 00:05:56,628
[♪ gentle music playing]

109
00:07:25,133 --> 00:07:27,051
Make sure not to get any water on it.

110
00:07:27,135 --> 00:07:30,138
You'll have to get it dressed every day
until the stitches are removed.

111
00:07:30,889 --> 00:07:34,768
To be honest, I used to think
the PH docs were pathetic.

112
00:07:35,518 --> 00:07:38,104
I couldn't help but wonder
how they had become doctors

113
00:07:38,188 --> 00:07:40,190
when they couldn't even
do a drill properly.

114
00:07:40,273 --> 00:07:42,567
[chuckles] Well, we're more accustomed
to studying at a desk, so…

115
00:07:42,650 --> 00:07:44,444
But I was wrong.

116
00:07:45,069 --> 00:07:48,281
The way you ran over to us
without any hesitation…

117
00:07:49,699 --> 00:07:51,326
You were like superheroes.

118
00:07:51,409 --> 00:07:54,662
IT IS OUR DUTY
TO SAVE OUR COMRADES' LIVES

119
00:07:54,746 --> 00:07:55,789
Thank you.

120
00:07:55,872 --> 00:07:57,540
2ND TRAINING BATTALION BARRACKS

121
00:07:57,624 --> 00:07:59,417
Where are you thinking of applying?

122
00:08:00,418 --> 00:08:02,545
Well, it's not like
things would go my way,

123
00:08:02,629 --> 00:08:04,631
since it's all up to the luck of the draw.

124
00:08:04,714 --> 00:08:05,965
I'm fine anywhere but an island.

125
00:08:06,049 --> 00:08:07,759
True. Islands are the worst.

126
00:08:08,593 --> 00:08:11,471
But if you do end up going to one,
be wary of three things.

127
00:08:12,889 --> 00:08:15,016
Three things?

128
00:08:15,099 --> 00:08:16,476
What three things?

129
00:08:16,559 --> 00:08:17,977
It's just something I heard.

130
00:08:18,061 --> 00:08:21,064
They say there are three things
that'll make your life a living hell.

131
00:08:21,147 --> 00:08:24,484
Incidents, people, and love.

132
00:08:24,567 --> 00:08:27,445
And if you get caught up in all three,
you'll never escape.
STYLE
::cue()

133
00:08:29,697 --> 00:08:34,911
Incidents, people, and love?

134
00:08:37,956 --> 00:08:39,749
[officer 4] Trainees!

135
00:08:39,833 --> 00:08:41,376
Which one of you was chatting?

136
00:08:41,459 --> 00:08:43,628
-I'm sorry, sir!
-Why are you dressed like that?

137
00:08:43,711 --> 00:08:44,796
Where's your cap?

138
00:08:44,879 --> 00:08:46,965
My cap? Oh, my cap…

139
00:08:47,048 --> 00:08:48,174
[officer 4] Why, you little!

140
00:08:48,258 --> 00:08:50,885
-Down on the ground!
-[soldiers] Down on the ground!

141
00:08:52,011 --> 00:08:55,306
On one, "Dress code."
On two, "Violation." One!

142
00:08:55,390 --> 00:08:56,516
[all] Dress code!

143
00:08:56,599 --> 00:08:58,476
-Two!
-Violation!

144
00:08:58,560 --> 00:09:00,645
-One!
-Dress code!

145
00:09:00,728 --> 00:09:02,897
-Two!
-Violation!

146
00:09:02,981 --> 00:09:04,107
-One!
-Dress code!

147
00:09:04,190 --> 00:09:05,191
[doctor] No way.

148
00:09:06,067 --> 00:09:07,986
There's no way I'd end up on an island.

149
00:09:08,695 --> 00:09:10,864
I couldn't possibly be that unlucky.

150
00:09:17,704 --> 00:09:18,830
I…

151
00:09:19,497 --> 00:09:20,707
was that unlucky.

152
00:09:20,790 --> 00:09:22,167
[ship horn blowing]

153
00:09:22,250 --> 00:09:23,626
YEOPOONG MARINE TRANSPORT

154
00:09:23,710 --> 00:09:29,007
EPISODE 1
THE DOCTOR SENT TO THE ISLAND

155
00:09:29,632 --> 00:09:32,177
Wow, for real? Okay.

156
00:09:32,844 --> 00:09:34,846
I guess I should go.

157
00:09:37,974 --> 00:09:39,601
I really don't think I can do this.

158
00:09:39,684 --> 00:09:42,187
Seriously, I really don't think I can go.

159
00:09:43,021 --> 00:09:44,564
You have to go, dumbass.

160
00:09:44,647 --> 00:09:46,024
What else can you do?

161
00:09:48,693 --> 00:09:49,694
Oh, man…

162
00:09:50,195 --> 00:09:53,198
[phone buzzing]

163
00:09:58,786 --> 00:09:59,787
Hey, Gangseok.

164
00:09:59,871 --> 00:10:01,122
Are you leaving now?

165
00:10:01,206 --> 00:10:02,415
[doctor] Yeah.

166
00:10:02,498 --> 00:10:03,750
You're in for a rough time.

167
00:10:04,500 --> 00:10:06,711
-How about your meds?
-Not yet.

168
00:10:06,794 --> 00:10:09,756
Those meds can cause side effects
like memory loss, dizziness,

169
00:10:09,839 --> 00:10:13,384
and hallucinations,
so not taking them would be ideal.

170
00:10:13,468 --> 00:10:14,469
I know.

171
00:10:15,220 --> 00:10:18,514
You heard the news about Hwayeong, right?

172
00:10:20,308 --> 00:10:23,519
Hey, so things haven't changed
between you guys?

173
00:10:23,603 --> 00:10:25,605
It's been a long time since Seonu left.

174
00:10:26,689 --> 00:10:28,107
So much time has passed…

175
00:10:28,191 --> 00:10:29,651
So what if time has passed?

176
00:10:31,110 --> 00:10:33,488
Scars aren't something
that heal over time.

177
00:10:34,239 --> 00:10:35,365
Scars…

178
00:10:37,325 --> 00:10:38,701
are healed with money.

179
00:10:40,578 --> 00:10:43,373
If you're worried about my scars,
shut your mouth and open your wallet.

180
00:10:44,290 --> 00:10:46,376
-[Gangseok] Hello? Jiui.
-Yeah.

181
00:10:46,459 --> 00:10:48,461
-Good luck out there.
-Thanks, Gangseok.

182
00:10:48,544 --> 00:10:49,545
Sure.

183
00:10:50,672 --> 00:10:52,465
[ship horn blows]

184
00:10:53,925 --> 00:10:55,510
[♪ gentle music plays]

185
00:11:17,407 --> 00:11:21,536
[announcer on PA] The ship bound for
Pyeondongdo, Pyeondongdo is now departing.

186
00:11:21,619 --> 00:11:23,329
Go. You have to go, you crazy bastard.

187
00:11:23,413 --> 00:11:27,333
All remaining passengers,
please board the ship at this time.

188
00:11:27,417 --> 00:11:29,043
[♪ eerie music plays]

189
00:11:29,127 --> 00:11:33,381
The ship bound for Pyeondongdo,
Pyeondongdo is now departing.

190
00:11:33,965 --> 00:11:36,092
All remaining passengers…

191
00:11:40,471 --> 00:11:42,473
[distorted audio]

192
00:11:50,481 --> 00:11:52,483
[breathing heavily]

193
00:11:55,486 --> 00:11:56,821
Please…

194
00:11:58,364 --> 00:11:59,615
[panting]

195
00:12:01,159 --> 00:12:03,328
DO JI UI, M
ELLMARP

196
00:12:10,043 --> 00:12:11,586
[Jiui, normal] Two hours to Pyeondongdo.

197
00:12:14,964 --> 00:12:16,382
All I have to do is fall asleep.

198
00:12:17,675 --> 00:12:19,093
Nothing's going to happen.

199
00:12:20,136 --> 00:12:21,220
Nothing.
STYLE
::cue()

200
00:12:36,194 --> 00:12:40,490
[ship horn blows]

201
00:12:52,960 --> 00:12:55,338
[passengers chattering]

202
00:12:55,421 --> 00:12:57,006
[passenger 1] We need to get
our numbers straight.

203
00:12:57,090 --> 00:12:58,424
Excuse me, young man.

204
00:12:58,508 --> 00:12:59,509
Hey, young man.

205
00:12:59,592 --> 00:13:01,094
Hey, open your eyes.

206
00:13:01,803 --> 00:13:03,888
[passenger 2] Young man!

207
00:13:03,971 --> 00:13:07,183
There's something we'd like to ask you.

208
00:13:07,266 --> 00:13:09,310
[muffled] My friend here
didn't have any cash,

209
00:13:09,394 --> 00:13:12,105
so she agreed to pay us back later
and borrowed…

210
00:13:12,188 --> 00:13:13,439
[distorted dialogue]

211
00:13:15,441 --> 00:13:17,193
That leaves 3,000 won, right?

212
00:13:17,276 --> 00:13:18,486
[breathes heavily]

213
00:13:19,570 --> 00:13:20,571
[grunts]

214
00:13:21,197 --> 00:13:23,408
[♪ eerie music plays]

215
00:13:40,967 --> 00:13:41,968
[normal] That's…

216
00:13:43,010 --> 00:13:44,178
dangerous.

217
00:13:45,638 --> 00:13:47,431
[breathing heavily]

218
00:13:53,187 --> 00:13:54,480
[groans]

219
00:14:08,578 --> 00:14:10,037
Excuse me.

220
00:14:13,624 --> 00:14:15,126
Excuse me!

221
00:14:17,795 --> 00:14:19,589
That's dangerous. Get down from there now.

222
00:14:19,672 --> 00:14:21,174
-[ship horn blows]
-[Jiui] Whoa.

223
00:14:21,257 --> 00:14:23,176
Don't step any closer.

224
00:14:23,259 --> 00:14:25,136
Don't do it. Get down from there!

225
00:14:45,740 --> 00:14:46,741
Hey!

226
00:14:49,702 --> 00:14:50,828
No.

227
00:14:53,664 --> 00:14:56,125
[♪ somber music plays]

228
00:15:12,600 --> 00:15:13,893
Someone's fallen overboard!

229
00:15:13,976 --> 00:15:15,603
Stop the boat!

230
00:15:17,730 --> 00:15:19,774
I said someone's fallen overboard!

231
00:15:44,715 --> 00:15:46,717
[♪ ethereal music playing]

232
00:16:18,749 --> 00:16:19,792
[chuckles]
STYLE
::cue()

233
00:16:36,934 --> 00:16:40,438
Take three steps outside,
and you'll find fish everywhere.

234
00:16:40,521 --> 00:16:42,773
So why are you looking
at the fish inside a tank?

235
00:16:42,857 --> 00:16:45,818
Come on, these guys
are different from those guys.

236
00:16:46,736 --> 00:16:49,655
They're raised for consumption.
These guys are meant for observing.

237
00:16:49,739 --> 00:16:51,866
They're totally different.

238
00:16:53,034 --> 00:16:55,745
Why are you even ranking fish?

239
00:16:55,828 --> 00:16:58,164
Whether they live
in seawater or tap water,

240
00:16:58,247 --> 00:17:00,041
they all live in water just the same.

241
00:17:00,124 --> 00:17:03,419
Oh, right.
You saw my leave request, right?

242
00:17:03,502 --> 00:17:07,131
Hey, I told you to put in requests
at least three days in advance, didn't I?

243
00:17:07,214 --> 00:17:10,259
[clicks tongue] I'll take care of it
this time, but don't let it happen again.

244
00:17:11,302 --> 00:17:13,054
Okay. Thank you.

245
00:17:15,389 --> 00:17:16,766
[nurse 1] Granny.

246
00:17:16,849 --> 00:17:18,017
-Granny Sunja.
-[Sunja] Yes?

247
00:17:18,100 --> 00:17:19,769
-Let's have you go inside.
-Okay.

248
00:17:19,852 --> 00:17:21,312
-Is it that room?
-Yes.

249
00:17:21,395 --> 00:17:24,231
[nurse 1] I've opened the door,
so all you need to do is step inside.

250
00:17:24,315 --> 00:17:26,859
[nurse 2] We haven't heard from
the new doctor yet, have we?

251
00:17:26,942 --> 00:17:28,986
No. They said
the ferry already arrived, though.

252
00:17:29,070 --> 00:17:31,405
Mmm. Must've been a paddle boat.

253
00:17:31,489 --> 00:17:33,908
[scoffs] Think he might have gotten lost?

254
00:17:33,991 --> 00:17:36,160
A smart doctor getting lost?

255
00:17:36,243 --> 00:17:39,246
On this tiny island?

256
00:17:39,330 --> 00:17:41,374
I'm telling you,
he's definitely taken a detour.

257
00:17:41,999 --> 00:17:43,459
Should I try giving him a call?

258
00:17:43,542 --> 00:17:44,543
I'll do it.

259
00:17:46,128 --> 00:17:49,131
I'm going to give him an earful and
really straighten him out. [clears throat]

260
00:17:49,215 --> 00:17:50,591
PUBLIC HEALTH CENTER

261
00:17:50,675 --> 00:17:52,134
[line ringing]

262
00:17:53,386 --> 00:17:56,806
[phone ringing]

263
00:17:56,889 --> 00:17:58,808
[snores, grunts]

264
00:17:58,891 --> 00:17:59,892
Damn it.

265
00:18:05,731 --> 00:18:07,191
Hello?

266
00:18:07,274 --> 00:18:08,484
[nurse 2] Dr. Do Jiui?

267
00:18:09,777 --> 00:18:10,986
Yes, who is this?

268
00:18:11,654 --> 00:18:14,115
I'm calling from
the Pyeondongdo Public Health Center.

269
00:18:15,491 --> 00:18:17,743
What is the Pyeondongdo
Public Health Center?

270
00:18:18,953 --> 00:18:20,705
[knocks on door]

271
00:18:22,206 --> 00:18:23,791
Dr. Do Jiui?

272
00:18:24,542 --> 00:18:26,210
[gasps, breathes heavily]

273
00:18:29,046 --> 00:18:31,048
[♪ playful music plays]

274
00:18:35,511 --> 00:18:39,181
Goodness, I had no idea
you were already here.

275
00:18:39,265 --> 00:18:41,517
We've been looking all over for you.

276
00:18:41,600 --> 00:18:42,893
Ugh.

277
00:18:45,771 --> 00:18:47,523
[stutters] What happened?

278
00:18:47,606 --> 00:18:49,150
[stutters] How about that woman?

279
00:18:49,233 --> 00:18:50,735
Is she still alive?

280
00:18:50,818 --> 00:18:52,027
What is he rambling about?

281
00:18:52,528 --> 00:18:54,947
[chuckles] I guess you must've had
a pretty wild dream.

282
00:18:55,990 --> 00:18:57,199
-A dream?
-Oh, my.

283
00:18:57,283 --> 00:18:59,910
I heard someone passed out on the ferry,

284
00:18:59,994 --> 00:19:02,121
so I thought it might be
a tourist or a fisherman

285
00:19:02,204 --> 00:19:03,789
who had drunk too much.

286
00:19:03,873 --> 00:19:06,917
Never did I guess
it would be our doctor. [chuckles]

287
00:19:07,960 --> 00:19:09,962
Wait, so that was really a dream?

288
00:19:10,045 --> 00:19:13,132
Mmm. That's enough.
It's time for you to wake up.

289
00:19:13,215 --> 00:19:14,800
I'll show you the health center.

290
00:19:14,884 --> 00:19:18,095
You'll be here for a year,
so you should get familiar with the place.

291
00:19:19,221 --> 00:19:20,681
-Right.
-Come on.

292
00:19:24,769 --> 00:19:25,770
Here.

293
00:19:26,437 --> 00:19:29,523
[yelps] He's coming out right on time.
Please introduce yourselves.

294
00:19:29,607 --> 00:19:32,401
This is Dr. Yong Jucheon
from the Korean Medicine ward.

295
00:19:32,485 --> 00:19:34,612
This here is our new surgeon, Dr. Do Jiui.

296
00:19:35,196 --> 00:19:36,197
Hello.

297
00:19:36,280 --> 00:19:37,573
Ooh!

298
00:19:37,656 --> 00:19:39,366
You were carried in earlier, right?

299
00:19:39,450 --> 00:19:42,369
[chuckles] So you're a doctor
assigned here, huh?

300
00:19:42,453 --> 00:19:43,954
We're really glad to have you.

301
00:19:44,038 --> 00:19:45,456
Hold on.

302
00:19:45,539 --> 00:19:47,124
If you're a doctor, here.

303
00:19:47,875 --> 00:19:50,419
-Sorry?
-[Jucheon] I'm asking for your number.

304
00:19:50,503 --> 00:19:54,131
It's hard adjusting to life here
when you've arrived from the city.

305
00:19:54,215 --> 00:19:57,301
One for regional PH docs,
one for us here, our public health center,

306
00:19:57,384 --> 00:19:59,595
Youth Association, Women's Association…

307
00:19:59,678 --> 00:20:01,680
Anyway, I'll invite you
to all the group chats.

308
00:20:01,764 --> 00:20:03,974
People live here
just like any other place.

309
00:20:04,058 --> 00:20:06,018
How different could it be?

310
00:20:06,101 --> 00:20:09,480
Stop making such a big fuss,
and take it slow with stuff like that.

311
00:20:09,563 --> 00:20:11,524
We haven't even shown him his office yet.

312
00:20:11,607 --> 00:20:13,734
Your office is that way.

313
00:20:13,818 --> 00:20:15,152
Exam room number one.

314
00:20:15,236 --> 00:20:17,196
We gave you the biggest room.

315
00:20:17,279 --> 00:20:20,241
Since you're a medical specialist.
[chuckles]

316
00:20:20,324 --> 00:20:22,910
Here, this way. You should see your room.

317
00:20:25,454 --> 00:20:27,706
A mercury sphygmomanometer.
STYLE
::cue()

318
00:20:28,999 --> 00:20:31,210
It's a bit outdated, isn't it? [chuckles]

319
00:20:31,877 --> 00:20:35,422
We do bring it up every year,
but nothing ever changes.

320
00:20:36,006 --> 00:20:39,260
I know it's rather shoddy compared
to the university hospitals in Seoul,

321
00:20:39,343 --> 00:20:42,179
but I doubt you'll have any major issues.

322
00:20:42,263 --> 00:20:45,349
The patients who visit our center

323
00:20:45,432 --> 00:20:48,686
don't come here
because of anything bad in particular,

324
00:20:48,769 --> 00:20:50,479
but because of chronic illnesses.

325
00:20:50,563 --> 00:20:51,981
Blood pressure, diabetes, and arthritis.

326
00:20:52,064 --> 00:20:55,526
They just live with those conditions
their whole lives. [chuckles]

327
00:20:55,609 --> 00:20:58,821
One granny said she hurt everywhere
except her eyebrows. [laughs]

328
00:20:59,905 --> 00:21:01,699
We should still get a new BP monitor.

329
00:21:04,201 --> 00:21:05,619
Right.

330
00:21:13,502 --> 00:21:15,921
[clears throat] You've seen
pretty much everything now.

331
00:21:16,005 --> 00:21:17,756
Should I get you something to drink?

332
00:21:18,340 --> 00:21:20,009
No, I just want to wash up right now.

333
00:21:20,092 --> 00:21:22,845
Uh. Here, your key.

334
00:21:22,928 --> 00:21:24,305
Right.

335
00:21:24,388 --> 00:21:28,309
To get to your room,
go up like this, go up like this,

336
00:21:28,392 --> 00:21:30,936
then go up like this,
and it's the first room on the left.

337
00:21:33,814 --> 00:21:34,815
[grunts]

338
00:21:35,691 --> 00:21:37,192
[exhales] Man, that's a lot better.

339
00:21:38,027 --> 00:21:39,028
[chittering]

340
00:21:39,111 --> 00:21:41,113
[♪ whimsical music plays]

341
00:21:48,954 --> 00:21:50,372
[chittering]

342
00:22:00,716 --> 00:22:01,717
[yelps]

343
00:22:03,344 --> 00:22:04,887
[grunts]

344
00:22:09,683 --> 00:22:11,143
[panting]

345
00:22:15,814 --> 00:22:16,941
What happened?

346
00:22:17,024 --> 00:22:18,567
There was a centipede this big!

347
00:22:18,651 --> 00:22:20,569
It fell on my face and… [panting]

348
00:22:20,653 --> 00:22:21,737
My goodness.

349
00:22:21,820 --> 00:22:24,281
And here I was thinking
it was something serious.

350
00:22:24,365 --> 00:22:26,408
I bet the centipede
was more startled than you.

351
00:22:26,492 --> 00:22:30,371
Centipedes aren't the only things here.
And they're tame compared to the rest.

352
00:22:30,454 --> 00:22:33,082
Snakes, house centipedes, spiders…

353
00:22:33,749 --> 00:22:36,418
Just think of them as your roommates.

354
00:22:36,502 --> 00:22:38,170
BUG SPRAY

355
00:22:49,598 --> 00:22:50,849
[shushes]

356
00:22:51,892 --> 00:22:53,936
[coughs]

357
00:23:14,999 --> 00:23:17,251
Oh. This isn't mine.

358
00:23:30,389 --> 00:23:31,390
No way.

359
00:23:32,433 --> 00:23:33,809
That woman with the bottle?

360
00:23:33,892 --> 00:23:35,144
[grunting]

361
00:23:38,856 --> 00:23:40,941
[panting]

362
00:23:45,946 --> 00:23:47,364
What now?

363
00:23:47,448 --> 00:23:48,699
Another bug?

364
00:23:48,782 --> 00:23:49,783
No.

365
00:23:49,867 --> 00:23:52,828
I think my suitcase got swapped,
and I'm not sure what to do.

366
00:23:52,911 --> 00:23:54,747
It's one thing after another
with this guy.

367
00:23:54,830 --> 00:23:58,042
For that, you'll have to go
to the village hall.

368
00:23:58,125 --> 00:24:00,753
If you tell
the Youth Association members there,

369
00:24:00,836 --> 00:24:02,921
they'll help you out
with just about anything.

370
00:24:03,005 --> 00:24:04,006
Go there.

371
00:24:04,089 --> 00:24:06,175
The village hall? Okay. Thank you.
STYLE
::cue()

372
00:24:06,258 --> 00:24:08,260
[♪ amusing music plays]

373
00:24:09,428 --> 00:24:10,429
Oh, man.

374
00:24:24,902 --> 00:24:27,279
[Jiui exclaims]

375
00:24:27,362 --> 00:24:30,240
Are you kidding me right now? [coughs]

376
00:24:33,535 --> 00:24:35,829
What's a car like that
doing on an island like this?

377
00:24:36,330 --> 00:24:38,540
PUBLIC HEALTH CENTER

378
00:24:38,624 --> 00:24:40,501
-Thanks for your hard work.
-Sure.

379
00:24:41,335 --> 00:24:42,669
How did the home visit go?

380
00:24:43,420 --> 00:24:45,923
How was the granny doing?
Is she better now?

381
00:24:46,006 --> 00:24:47,341
Yes, she's better now.

382
00:24:49,468 --> 00:24:53,764
Ms. Hwang, what exactly
are the criteria for home visits?

383
00:24:53,847 --> 00:24:55,182
What do you mean by that?

384
00:24:55,766 --> 00:24:58,018
I just don't think it's fair
that even the patients

385
00:24:58,102 --> 00:25:00,270
who are perfectly capable
of getting around

386
00:25:00,354 --> 00:25:01,730
get to apply for home visits.

387
00:25:01,814 --> 00:25:02,981
[Ms. Hwang] Ah.

388
00:25:03,607 --> 00:25:06,610
Right, it can be unfair.

389
00:25:06,693 --> 00:25:08,695
But such are human affairs.

390
00:25:08,779 --> 00:25:11,657
Not everything can be
perfectly fair, you know?

391
00:25:11,740 --> 00:25:13,033
Yes.

392
00:25:14,535 --> 00:25:16,954
Then I'll be turning down home visits.

393
00:25:17,621 --> 00:25:18,622
What?

394
00:25:18,705 --> 00:25:22,042
To my understanding, PH docs
aren't obligated to perform home visits.

395
00:25:30,050 --> 00:25:32,219
Wow, that guy…

396
00:25:32,302 --> 00:25:34,555
PYEONDONGDO VILLAGE HALL

397
00:25:35,472 --> 00:25:39,309
So, your suitcase got mixed up
with someone else's on the ferry?

398
00:25:39,393 --> 00:25:41,520
Yes. I think it got mixed up
with some woman's.

399
00:25:41,603 --> 00:25:43,355
She had short hair.

400
00:25:44,898 --> 00:25:46,400
By the way,

401
00:25:46,483 --> 00:25:49,361
weren't there any accidents
involving one of the passengers?

402
00:25:49,444 --> 00:25:51,780
Like someone falling into the water or…

403
00:25:51,864 --> 00:25:54,449
We've never had accidents
involving passengers.

404
00:25:54,533 --> 00:25:58,036
Our ferry, the Hansol No. 3,
has been accident-free for 20 years.

405
00:25:59,955 --> 00:26:01,248
Hold on.

406
00:26:01,331 --> 00:26:04,293
It must have gotten mixed up
with Granny Mija's granddaughter's.

407
00:26:05,544 --> 00:26:06,795
Sorry? Granddaughter?

408
00:26:06,879 --> 00:26:10,424
Oh, my. You must really
not remember, Doctor.

409
00:26:11,466 --> 00:26:15,429
The one who carried you on her back
was Granny Mija's granddaughter.

410
00:26:15,512 --> 00:26:17,264
-Granddaughter?
-But anyway,

411
00:26:17,347 --> 00:26:19,683
if you're a doctor, why are you so feeble?

412
00:26:19,766 --> 00:26:22,394
Hey, quit it!

413
00:26:22,477 --> 00:26:24,146
That's how your suitcase got mixed up.

414
00:26:24,229 --> 00:26:26,940
So the one who carried me was a woman?

415
00:26:30,694 --> 00:26:33,530
I mean, all these houses
have red rooftops.

416
00:26:34,615 --> 00:26:37,034
Which red rooftop were they talking about?

417
00:26:39,786 --> 00:26:42,331
And what does "follow the road
and go straight" mean?

418
00:26:42,414 --> 00:26:44,041
I've been walking straight forever.

419
00:26:44,124 --> 00:26:46,627
[bypasser 1 screaming] Help!

420
00:26:47,628 --> 00:26:48,879
Move!

421
00:26:52,216 --> 00:26:53,717
Run!

422
00:26:53,800 --> 00:26:55,260
[♪ gentle music plays]

423
00:26:56,553 --> 00:27:00,474
[barking, growling]
STYLE
::cue()

424
00:27:40,597 --> 00:27:43,058
-Hurry! This way!
-Run!

425
00:27:47,229 --> 00:27:49,064
[shrieking]

426
00:27:49,982 --> 00:27:52,234
-[screaming]
-No!

427
00:28:00,993 --> 00:28:03,620
Deokgu!

428
00:28:03,704 --> 00:28:05,998
Goodness me, where did you go?

429
00:28:06,081 --> 00:28:08,792
Oh, no, Deokgu!

430
00:28:08,875 --> 00:28:11,169
I'm sorry!

431
00:28:11,253 --> 00:28:13,171
I was wondering where you had run off to.

432
00:28:13,255 --> 00:28:15,257
-Come here. Gosh, I'm sorry.
-Deokgu?

433
00:28:15,340 --> 00:28:17,884
-Deokgu?
-Where have you been?

434
00:28:18,802 --> 00:28:20,262
Come here.

435
00:28:20,345 --> 00:28:21,346
You bad boy. Let's go.

436
00:28:21,430 --> 00:28:22,848
-Come on.
-Auntie!

437
00:28:24,141 --> 00:28:26,685
[stutters] You're Hari, aren't you?

438
00:28:26,768 --> 00:28:31,523
-[yelps] Auntie! I'm so happy to see you!
-Oh, my!

439
00:28:31,606 --> 00:28:33,108
Have you been well?

440
00:28:33,191 --> 00:28:34,484
What are you doing here?

441
00:28:34,568 --> 00:28:35,569
[giggles]

442
00:28:36,069 --> 00:28:38,321
Deokgu's grown so big. Hi, Deokgu.

443
00:28:38,405 --> 00:28:40,282
-[Hari] You're still cute.
-That's a friendly dog.

444
00:28:52,002 --> 00:28:53,712
[grunts] Gosh, I'm sorry.

445
00:28:55,714 --> 00:28:58,717
I must have taken your suitcase
because I was so out of it. [chuckles]

446
00:28:59,384 --> 00:29:00,594
Check this one too.

447
00:29:00,677 --> 00:29:02,012
I'm sure it's mine.

448
00:29:02,095 --> 00:29:03,513
Well, you should still check.

449
00:29:03,597 --> 00:29:05,766
I opened it briefly.
The lock code was the same.

450
00:29:05,849 --> 00:29:08,685
Wow, then I guess
we must have the same birthday.

451
00:29:09,770 --> 00:29:11,271
November 6th?

452
00:29:11,354 --> 00:29:12,731
No, January 16th.

453
00:29:12,814 --> 00:29:14,232
I see. [chuckles]

454
00:29:28,413 --> 00:29:30,123
Oh, my. Why are these…

455
00:29:34,544 --> 00:29:36,630
MEDICAL PATCH
NARCOTIC PAINKILLERS

456
00:29:36,713 --> 00:29:38,298
CHAVOXIFEN
CHAVOXIFEN CITRATE

457
00:29:38,381 --> 00:29:39,758
[Jiui] "Chavoxifen"?

458
00:29:40,842 --> 00:29:43,804
That's a targeted agent.

459
00:29:44,679 --> 00:29:46,681
[♪ somber music plays]

460
00:29:54,189 --> 00:29:55,899
Looks like everything's here.

461
00:30:00,362 --> 00:30:02,823
[chittering]

462
00:30:02,906 --> 00:30:04,116
[exclaims]

463
00:30:04,199 --> 00:30:05,826
-That's where it was.
-What's wrong?

464
00:30:05,909 --> 00:30:07,828
-Damn it.
-What?

465
00:30:09,246 --> 00:30:11,998
-Goodness, let me get that for you.
-Okay.

466
00:30:18,338 --> 00:30:20,006
Good. [chuckles]

467
00:30:21,133 --> 00:30:22,217
It's fine.

468
00:30:25,345 --> 00:30:26,721
All done.

469
00:30:26,805 --> 00:30:27,806
Right.

470
00:30:28,640 --> 00:30:31,518
Mine's good to go.
Shouldn't you check yours?

471
00:30:33,728 --> 00:30:34,855
Right.

472
00:30:44,948 --> 00:30:47,450
[♪ soft guitar plays]

473
00:30:53,790 --> 00:30:55,041
Oh, right.

474
00:30:56,793 --> 00:30:58,503
This also belongs to you, right?

475
00:30:58,587 --> 00:31:00,297
ELLMARP

476
00:31:00,380 --> 00:31:03,216
[sighs] Thank you.
STYLE
::cue()

477
00:31:05,260 --> 00:31:06,928
Don't take that medication.

478
00:31:08,763 --> 00:31:10,932
I don't think it agrees with you.

479
00:31:11,016 --> 00:31:13,018
You were in serious danger
on the ferry earlier.

480
00:31:13,685 --> 00:31:14,686
[scoffs]

481
00:31:15,604 --> 00:31:16,605
Wait…

482
00:31:17,606 --> 00:31:20,942
Look who's talking about being in danger.

483
00:31:21,026 --> 00:31:22,402
[stutters] What?

484
00:31:22,485 --> 00:31:24,279
What were you doing up there anyway?

485
00:31:24,362 --> 00:31:26,823
Were you trying to kill yourself?

486
00:31:26,907 --> 00:31:27,908
Me?

487
00:31:28,617 --> 00:31:29,618
Why on earth would I--

488
00:31:29,701 --> 00:31:32,204
I got into this whole mess
because I tried to save you.

489
00:31:32,787 --> 00:31:35,874
[chuckles] What the heck
are you talking about?

490
00:31:37,459 --> 00:31:39,461
[♪ intriguing music plays]

491
00:31:41,254 --> 00:31:43,632
Ms. Mija, it's so pretty out here!

492
00:31:43,715 --> 00:31:45,217
Check out the ocean.

493
00:31:45,300 --> 00:31:49,512
Goodness, what beauty is there
in something I see every day?

494
00:31:49,596 --> 00:31:53,016
To me, you're the prettiest thing
in the world, Hari.

495
00:31:53,099 --> 00:31:57,020
[Hari] Hey, I take after my grandma.
Of course I'm pretty.

496
00:31:57,103 --> 00:31:58,188
[groaning]

497
00:31:59,189 --> 00:32:00,565
[Hari] Grandma, have you eaten yet?

498
00:32:04,778 --> 00:32:06,988
-My cardigan went flying.
-[Jiui groaning]

499
00:32:07,072 --> 00:32:09,950
-[Hari] I'll just have to get a new one.
-Hey, don't!

500
00:32:10,617 --> 00:32:11,952
[Hari yelps]

501
00:32:12,035 --> 00:32:14,621
No, don't!

502
00:32:14,704 --> 00:32:15,705
What?

503
00:32:15,789 --> 00:32:18,875
-Don't go.
-Oh, no. You have to be careful.

504
00:32:18,959 --> 00:32:20,335
It's dangerous up there!

505
00:32:20,418 --> 00:32:22,587
-Over here!
-What?

506
00:32:22,671 --> 00:32:25,382
[Jiui] I need help over here!

507
00:32:26,383 --> 00:32:27,467
Someone…

508
00:32:27,550 --> 00:32:29,636
Someone's fallen into the water!

509
00:32:29,719 --> 00:32:32,222
I think we have to stop the boat!

510
00:32:32,305 --> 00:32:33,932
What did you say?

511
00:32:34,015 --> 00:32:36,851
-I'll… I'll save her.
-[Hari] Careful!

512
00:32:36,935 --> 00:32:38,979
-I'll save you!
-Who are you trying to save?

513
00:32:40,313 --> 00:32:42,607
Oh, no. What do I do?

514
00:32:42,691 --> 00:32:44,693
-I'll save you!
-Wait!

515
00:32:44,776 --> 00:32:47,028
-[Jiui] No… Damn it.
-Just hold on!

516
00:33:07,716 --> 00:33:09,009
[scoffs]

517
00:33:09,801 --> 00:33:10,927
[stutters] I did that?

518
00:33:11,011 --> 00:33:13,430
[ship horn blows]

519
00:33:13,513 --> 00:33:17,017
[panting] I shouldn't have
knocked him out like that.

520
00:33:17,684 --> 00:33:20,228
Gosh, he's so freaking heavy. [panting]

521
00:33:21,938 --> 00:33:25,275
Excuse me, please wake up.

522
00:33:25,358 --> 00:33:27,485
You really don't remember anything?

523
00:33:30,071 --> 00:33:32,407
I don't remember that at all. I don't.

524
00:33:36,369 --> 00:33:37,912
Are you better now?

525
00:33:37,996 --> 00:33:39,622
Gosh. I'm totally…

526
00:33:41,916 --> 00:33:43,585
-Are you leaving?
-Of course!

527
00:33:45,503 --> 00:33:46,504
[Hari] Take care!

528
00:33:49,549 --> 00:33:50,550
Oh, no.

529
00:33:58,641 --> 00:33:59,976
What's with that guy?

530
00:34:05,815 --> 00:34:08,068
[♪ gentle music plays]
STYLE
::cue()

531
00:34:08,151 --> 00:34:10,236
-[Mija] Yeah, on that side.
-[Hari] Yes.

532
00:34:10,320 --> 00:34:11,738
[Mija] Did you return his suitcase?

533
00:34:11,821 --> 00:34:12,822
[Hari] Yeah.

534
00:34:13,823 --> 00:34:15,784
And he didn't say anything weird?

535
00:34:15,867 --> 00:34:18,244
Sounded like he wasn't normal.

536
00:34:18,328 --> 00:34:19,662
Yeah, he's a total weirdo.

537
00:34:19,746 --> 00:34:22,832
You said you were going back
to the mainland again tomorrow.

538
00:34:22,916 --> 00:34:25,210
Why did you have to move your bags today

539
00:34:25,293 --> 00:34:27,295
and get mixed up with a guy like that?

540
00:34:27,379 --> 00:34:30,173
Tomorrow will come
with tomorrow's share of baggage.

541
00:34:30,256 --> 00:34:33,676
Why did you even come
all the way back to this island?

542
00:34:33,760 --> 00:34:35,929
Let's hurry. Mom and Dad must be hungry.

543
00:34:36,012 --> 00:34:38,723
Look at you. Fine, let's do that.

544
00:34:38,807 --> 00:34:39,808
Here we go.

545
00:34:43,019 --> 00:34:44,020
What the heck?

546
00:34:45,397 --> 00:34:47,107
Why's this thing open?

547
00:34:49,609 --> 00:34:52,028
No idea. I wonder why it was open.

548
00:34:52,112 --> 00:34:54,072
You drank from it, didn't you?

549
00:34:55,156 --> 00:34:56,157
[stammers]

550
00:34:56,241 --> 00:34:58,785
I only did it because I was thirsty.

551
00:34:58,868 --> 00:35:02,372
Goodness me. Who did you get that from?

552
00:35:02,455 --> 00:35:04,416
I got it all from you, Granny.

553
00:35:04,499 --> 00:35:06,459
-How are you so cute?
-[Hari giggles]

554
00:35:06,543 --> 00:35:08,378
I also got that all from you, Granny.

555
00:35:08,461 --> 00:35:10,380
My, my, you precious thing.

556
00:35:16,594 --> 00:35:19,472
Making up stories
just because I don't remember.

557
00:35:21,558 --> 00:35:24,018
Does she not realize
I ended up like that because of her?

558
00:35:24,102 --> 00:35:25,353
Man, this is just…

559
00:35:28,940 --> 00:35:31,818
PUBLIC HEALTH CENTER

560
00:35:31,901 --> 00:35:33,903
[♪ whimsical music playing]

561
00:35:35,113 --> 00:35:36,114
What the…

562
00:35:36,990 --> 00:35:39,534
-What's this car doing here?
-[engine revving]

563
00:35:44,205 --> 00:35:45,290
[grunts]

564
00:35:48,168 --> 00:35:49,169
[groans]

565
00:35:53,214 --> 00:35:54,215
BATHROOM

566
00:35:55,884 --> 00:35:57,886
[♪ sultry music playing]

567
00:36:10,607 --> 00:36:11,983
[music ends]

568
00:36:16,529 --> 00:36:19,824
I'm sorry. I thought
there was no one in here…

569
00:36:21,576 --> 00:36:23,453
You're the doctor who came today, right?

570
00:36:24,662 --> 00:36:26,664
Yes. I'm Do Jiui.

571
00:36:28,917 --> 00:36:30,043
I'm Hyeon Chiyeon.

572
00:36:34,631 --> 00:36:36,132
I heard you were carried here.

573
00:36:39,594 --> 00:36:40,929
I don't recall that.

574
00:36:42,764 --> 00:36:45,725
That's a relief.
I look forward to working with you.

575
00:36:51,105 --> 00:36:52,273
What the heck was that?

576
00:37:02,283 --> 00:37:03,284
[grunts]

577
00:37:06,496 --> 00:37:07,497
[sighs]

578
00:37:12,252 --> 00:37:14,254
[♪ sentimental music playing]

579
00:37:24,639 --> 00:37:25,640
Doctor.

580
00:37:27,392 --> 00:37:28,560
Aren't you hungry?

581
00:37:28,643 --> 00:37:31,396
You should treat us all
since it's your first day here.
STYLE
::cue()

582
00:37:33,273 --> 00:37:34,399
-Me?
-Yes.

583
00:37:34,482 --> 00:37:36,985
Dr. Chiyeon is waiting for you,
so hurry and come outside.

584
00:37:40,446 --> 00:37:41,948
Why should I be treating them?

585
00:37:42,657 --> 00:37:45,702
CLIFFSIDE RAW FISH RESTAURANT
BEST RESTAURANT IN PYEONDONGDO

586
00:37:45,785 --> 00:37:46,953
Hello.

587
00:37:48,663 --> 00:37:50,707
Auntie, we're here!

588
00:37:50,790 --> 00:37:52,250
[Geumja] Oh, you're here?

589
00:37:53,793 --> 00:37:55,587
It's so hot.

590
00:37:58,172 --> 00:37:59,799
-Oh, my.
-Huh?

591
00:37:59,883 --> 00:38:01,301
It's you again.

592
00:38:02,010 --> 00:38:04,554
-That was quite startling, wasn't it?
-Yes.

593
00:38:04,637 --> 00:38:06,681
-You two have already met?
-Yes.

594
00:38:06,764 --> 00:38:09,517
-[stutters] There was a minor incident.
-Ah.

595
00:38:10,101 --> 00:38:13,062
Auntie, we'll have the dish
that got rave reviews on that TV show.

596
00:38:13,146 --> 00:38:15,481
-The one we ordered in advance, please.
-Of course.

597
00:38:15,565 --> 00:38:17,150
-Just give me a moment.
-[Jucheon] Okay.

598
00:38:19,569 --> 00:38:21,404
What do you specialize in, Doctor?

599
00:38:22,322 --> 00:38:25,033
-Plastic surgery.
-Wow.

600
00:38:25,116 --> 00:38:28,328
You must have done very well in school.
Plastic surgery is so popular.

601
00:38:28,411 --> 00:38:29,412
Yes, well…

602
00:38:29,495 --> 00:38:32,165
You haven't chosen
your specialty yet, right?

603
00:38:32,248 --> 00:38:34,000
-That's right.
-Hmm.

604
00:38:34,083 --> 00:38:35,543
How about a plastic surgery clinic?

605
00:38:35,627 --> 00:38:38,796
If you opened a clinic in Gangnam,
I bet people would line up asking you

606
00:38:38,880 --> 00:38:41,174
to fix them up
to look like you. [chuckles]

607
00:38:42,425 --> 00:38:43,718
Hmm.

608
00:38:43,801 --> 00:38:45,303
I don't know.

609
00:38:45,386 --> 00:38:47,764
I'm not a huge fan of plastic surgeons.

610
00:38:48,348 --> 00:38:50,141
They just come across as money-grubbers.

611
00:38:51,643 --> 00:38:52,644
What did you say?

612
00:38:53,853 --> 00:38:55,939
Ah. I sure am hungry.

613
00:38:57,482 --> 00:38:59,108
Right to my face? Really?

614
00:38:59,192 --> 00:39:03,071
Here it comes, our signature dish.

615
00:39:04,489 --> 00:39:06,240
-Here you are.
-[Jucheon] Wow.

616
00:39:08,701 --> 00:39:10,703
[♪ intriguing music playing]

617
00:39:16,501 --> 00:39:18,127
[Geumja sighs]

618
00:39:20,713 --> 00:39:21,714
[Geumja exclaims]

619
00:39:22,465 --> 00:39:24,050
-Uh…
-It looks so good.

620
00:39:26,678 --> 00:39:27,679
[gags]

621
00:39:28,429 --> 00:39:30,056
-Thank you.
-[Geumja chuckles]

622
00:39:32,392 --> 00:39:34,268
And here's one for you, Doctor.

623
00:39:34,352 --> 00:39:35,853
Hurry up and eat.

624
00:39:35,937 --> 00:39:38,022
This is the only restaurant
in Pyeondongdo.

625
00:39:38,648 --> 00:39:42,193
If you don't hype it up,
you'll starve to death.

626
00:39:44,112 --> 00:39:45,655
[Geumja] There you go.

627
00:39:46,656 --> 00:39:49,325
-Yes, thank you.
-[Geumja] Enjoy.

628
00:39:51,828 --> 00:39:54,038
-[Geumja] Here.
-[Jucheon] Thank you.

629
00:39:54,789 --> 00:39:59,210
I don't know
if it'll suit your taste, Doctor.

630
00:40:00,294 --> 00:40:01,295
Hurry.

631
00:40:01,379 --> 00:40:04,590
Your only source of sustenance
for a whole year rests on it.

632
00:40:10,179 --> 00:40:11,264
[sighs]

633
00:40:14,475 --> 00:40:15,768
[chuckles] Eat up.

634
00:40:15,852 --> 00:40:18,855
[♪ tense music playing]

635
00:40:26,946 --> 00:40:29,449
-[Jiui exclaims]
-Eh?

636
00:40:29,532 --> 00:40:31,159
[Jucheon chuckles]

637
00:40:33,161 --> 00:40:34,162
[landline ringing]

638
00:40:38,750 --> 00:40:40,918
[Geumja] Yes, this is Cliffside.

639
00:40:41,002 --> 00:40:42,003
Yes.

640
00:40:42,670 --> 00:40:43,671
What?

641
00:40:44,172 --> 00:40:45,882
They're all here.

642
00:40:45,965 --> 00:40:46,966
Okay.

643
00:40:47,800 --> 00:40:50,803
The chief is asking for one doctor
back at the center…

644
00:40:50,887 --> 00:40:52,513
-I'll go.
-[Jucheon] What?

645
00:40:52,597 --> 00:40:54,182
But it's your first day.

646
00:40:54,265 --> 00:40:57,018
What can I say? I'm a workaholic.
I'll finish it when I get back.
STYLE
::cue()

647
00:40:59,562 --> 00:41:01,564
[ship horn blares in distance]

648
00:41:07,904 --> 00:41:09,489
PUBLIC HEALTH CENTER

649
00:41:11,074 --> 00:41:12,200
Mr. Park.

650
00:41:12,283 --> 00:41:13,284
CLOSED

651
00:41:13,367 --> 00:41:14,619
Ah!

652
00:41:14,702 --> 00:41:18,164
Oh, Doctor. Did you find your suitcase?

653
00:41:18,247 --> 00:41:21,501
Yes, thanks to you.
But can you tell me how you're sick?

654
00:41:21,584 --> 00:41:26,631
[sighs] I think I have indigestion.
My chest is really stuffy.

655
00:41:26,714 --> 00:41:28,883
So, give me some Umetazole.

656
00:41:29,509 --> 00:41:31,344
-Umetazole?
-Ah.

657
00:41:31,844 --> 00:41:33,638
I think I have a bad case of indigestion.

658
00:41:33,721 --> 00:41:36,641
So bad that I threw up
everything I ate for breakfast.

659
00:41:37,266 --> 00:41:40,436
I have fishing customers coming,
so I have to get going right away.

660
00:41:40,520 --> 00:41:42,105
Please hurry and give it to me.

661
00:41:42,772 --> 00:41:45,149
Let's get inside
so I can take a look at you first.

662
00:41:45,233 --> 00:41:46,984
-Let's take this inside.
-Okay.

663
00:41:47,568 --> 00:41:48,986
[Chunsik groans]

664
00:41:50,238 --> 00:41:52,323
[sniffles] Here.

665
00:41:52,406 --> 00:41:53,825
The left side.

666
00:41:53,908 --> 00:41:55,910
My left arm's also really sore.

667
00:41:55,993 --> 00:41:57,620
It's killing me.

668
00:41:57,703 --> 00:41:59,872
Does it feel as if someone's wringing it?

669
00:41:59,956 --> 00:42:02,375
Yes. It does kind of feel like that.

670
00:42:03,084 --> 00:42:06,087
I must have serious indigestion.

671
00:42:06,170 --> 00:42:09,507
Just give me Umetazole.
I'll be fine once I take it.

672
00:42:09,590 --> 00:42:12,051
-I've always taken it.
-Let me take your blood pressure.

673
00:42:13,594 --> 00:42:15,138
Hey, now.

674
00:42:15,221 --> 00:42:18,141
I have indigestion.
Why even bother taking my blood pressure?

675
00:42:18,224 --> 00:42:20,226
[breathing heavily]

676
00:42:34,699 --> 00:42:37,201
[air hissing]

677
00:42:37,910 --> 00:42:39,912
[♪ tense music playing]

678
00:42:42,623 --> 00:42:45,376
[Jiui] Stuffiness in his left chest,
trouble breathing,

679
00:42:45,960 --> 00:42:49,338
chest pains that feel as though
someone's wringing his chest,

680
00:42:49,422 --> 00:42:54,552
high blood pressure, nausea,
and even referred pain in the left arm.

681
00:42:55,803 --> 00:42:57,180
All signs point to an MI.

682
00:42:57,263 --> 00:42:59,807
MI: MYOCARDIAL INFARCTION

683
00:43:06,522 --> 00:43:08,232
[inhales deeply] Wait here for a moment.

684
00:43:08,983 --> 00:43:09,984
[Chunsik] Okay.

685
00:43:28,002 --> 00:43:29,003
UMETAZOLE

686
00:43:33,382 --> 00:43:35,760
-Can you try taking this?
-Huh?

687
00:43:36,969 --> 00:43:39,055
[Jiui] Put it under your tongue,
and let it melt.

688
00:43:40,181 --> 00:43:41,182
Okay.

689
00:43:42,934 --> 00:43:43,935
[sighs]

690
00:43:45,311 --> 00:43:48,648
[breathing heavily]

691
00:43:52,360 --> 00:43:53,361
[exhales deeply]

692
00:43:55,279 --> 00:43:56,697
[sighs]

693
00:44:03,287 --> 00:44:04,747
[Chunsik groans]

694
00:44:05,248 --> 00:44:07,583
[breathes deeply]

695
00:44:09,293 --> 00:44:10,294
What the…

696
00:44:11,254 --> 00:44:13,047
I feel better already.

697
00:44:13,673 --> 00:44:15,424
[Jiui] He wasn't supposed to feel better.

698
00:44:15,508 --> 00:44:18,844
The fact that the NTG worked
within minutes means

699
00:44:19,428 --> 00:44:22,723
there's a higher than 80% chance that
we're looking at a myocardial infarction.
STYLE
::cue()

700
00:44:22,807 --> 00:44:25,393
PATIENT RECORD QUERY
MYOCARDIAL INFARCTION, NTG

701
00:44:25,476 --> 00:44:29,188
I thought you were a weakling
because a girl carried you here,

702
00:44:29,272 --> 00:44:31,399
but you're an amazing doctor. [chuckles]

703
00:44:31,482 --> 00:44:34,026
Pyeondongdo has nothing
to worry about now.

704
00:44:34,110 --> 00:44:38,614
If anything troubles you during your stay,
feel free to tell me about it.

705
00:44:39,365 --> 00:44:42,118
Now, I've got urgent business
to attend to, so I'll--

706
00:44:42,201 --> 00:44:44,120
No, you shouldn't leave right now.

707
00:44:44,203 --> 00:44:45,579
Why?

708
00:44:45,663 --> 00:44:47,373
That wasn't digestive medicine.

709
00:44:47,456 --> 00:44:49,458
It was a drug
for myocardial infarction patients.

710
00:44:50,293 --> 00:44:52,253
The fact that your condition improved

711
00:44:52,336 --> 00:44:55,673
means there's a higher than 80% chance
of you getting a heart attack.

712
00:44:55,756 --> 00:44:57,425
We have to get you to a big hospital.

713
00:44:57,508 --> 00:45:01,595
Oh, come on.
I see our new doctor's a total worrywart.

714
00:45:01,679 --> 00:45:04,181
A big hospital? Please, I'll be fine!

715
00:45:04,265 --> 00:45:06,309
I'm telling you, you have to go right now!

716
00:45:06,392 --> 00:45:09,061
Don't worry. I know my body best.

717
00:45:09,145 --> 00:45:10,187
Mr. Park!

718
00:45:10,271 --> 00:45:11,605
Move aside!

719
00:45:11,689 --> 00:45:14,650
If I get hit with a fee for bailing,
will you take responsibility?

720
00:45:14,734 --> 00:45:16,944
Keep this up
and something bad will happen to you.

721
00:45:17,028 --> 00:45:18,362
Geez. [sighs]

722
00:45:18,446 --> 00:45:22,450
Doctor, you said there was an 80% chance
of me getting a heart attack, right?

723
00:45:22,533 --> 00:45:25,328
But there's a 100% chance
of my fishing customers coming!

724
00:45:26,495 --> 00:45:27,872
-[sighs]
-Fine.

725
00:45:27,955 --> 00:45:31,334
I'll just give my customers a ride,
then go to a hospital, so move.

726
00:45:31,417 --> 00:45:32,877
You could end up passing away.

727
00:45:32,960 --> 00:45:34,170
What do you mean, pass…

728
00:45:39,925 --> 00:45:40,926
What now?

729
00:45:42,178 --> 00:45:43,179
Pass away?

730
00:45:43,888 --> 00:45:44,930
Yes.

731
00:45:48,142 --> 00:45:50,519
[exhales sharply] That's no good.

732
00:45:51,729 --> 00:45:52,730
What am I to do?

733
00:45:53,731 --> 00:45:54,732
So…

734
00:45:55,274 --> 00:45:57,318
You're saying I have to go no matter what?

735
00:46:03,157 --> 00:46:04,658
Okay.

736
00:46:04,742 --> 00:46:06,619
I should listen to you.

737
00:46:06,702 --> 00:46:09,372
Take a seat outside,
and I'll get right back to you.

738
00:46:09,455 --> 00:46:12,083
I guess I'll do that.

739
00:46:22,385 --> 00:46:23,386
[line ringing]

740
00:46:26,806 --> 00:46:28,891
Yes, Ms. Hwang.
We have an emergency patient.

741
00:46:28,974 --> 00:46:31,018
He's a myocardial infarction patient.
I'll…

742
00:46:31,602 --> 00:46:33,145
What? A chopper?

743
00:46:35,106 --> 00:46:36,690
Mr. Park, they're sending a chopper…

744
00:46:40,319 --> 00:46:41,320
Mr. Park?

745
00:46:47,535 --> 00:46:48,536
Mr. Park?

746
00:46:53,082 --> 00:46:54,417
Damn it.

747
00:46:55,084 --> 00:46:57,586
Trust me, I know my own body best.

748
00:47:01,006 --> 00:47:03,509
Goodness, I'm going to miss my customers.

749
00:47:06,470 --> 00:47:10,266
What do you mean
the patient's gone missing?

750
00:47:10,349 --> 00:47:12,518
He slipped out
while I was on the phone with you…

751
00:47:12,601 --> 00:47:14,728
-[gasps]
-What about the chopper?

752
00:47:14,812 --> 00:47:17,857
If we call one with no patient,
our center will be penalized.

753
00:47:17,940 --> 00:47:19,150
[Jiui] He'll get on that chopper.

754
00:47:19,233 --> 00:47:23,362
Given his response to NTG,
he may end up having a heart attack.

755
00:47:23,446 --> 00:47:25,531
So let's find him as quickly as we can.

756
00:47:26,115 --> 00:47:27,950
Is he not picking up his phone?

757
00:47:28,033 --> 00:47:30,035
Why isn't he answering his phone?

758
00:47:31,495 --> 00:47:33,581
-[stammers] The fishing boat.
-What?

759
00:47:33,664 --> 00:47:35,332
He said he had fishing customers.

760
00:47:35,416 --> 00:47:36,667
-Let's go!
-Let's hurry.

761
00:47:37,918 --> 00:47:39,128
Mr. Park!

762
00:47:40,004 --> 00:47:41,088
Mr. Park!

763
00:47:41,172 --> 00:47:42,173
Mr. Park!

764
00:47:44,008 --> 00:47:45,009
Mr. Park!
STYLE
::cue()

765
00:47:45,092 --> 00:47:46,135
Mr. Park!

766
00:47:49,054 --> 00:47:52,141
-Mr. Park!
-Mr. Park. Are you okay?

767
00:47:52,224 --> 00:47:53,851
You have to come with us right now.

768
00:47:53,934 --> 00:47:55,603
What brings you all here?

769
00:47:55,686 --> 00:47:57,521
Doesn't your body feel kind of iffy?

770
00:47:57,605 --> 00:48:01,442
Why the hell did you all follow me here?
I told you I'm fine, didn't I?

771
00:48:01,525 --> 00:48:03,402
I know my body best!

772
00:48:03,486 --> 00:48:06,238
-But still, you should…
-Mr. Park, that's all temporary.

773
00:48:06,322 --> 00:48:07,531
-You--
-I've heard enough.

774
00:48:07,615 --> 00:48:10,409
Just go about your business. I said, go!

775
00:48:10,493 --> 00:48:12,453
-I'm hella busy, okay?
-Okay.

776
00:48:12,536 --> 00:48:14,038
Then just a quick check.

777
00:48:14,121 --> 00:48:17,166
I'm fine! Just go.

778
00:48:17,249 --> 00:48:19,251
Hello, sir, come this way.

779
00:48:19,335 --> 00:48:20,878
This way. Get on the boat.

780
00:48:20,961 --> 00:48:23,756
-I said go away.
-Okay.

781
00:48:23,839 --> 00:48:25,174
I'm fine!

782
00:48:25,257 --> 00:48:26,884
-Okay.
-Here, get in.

783
00:48:26,967 --> 00:48:28,385
-This one, right?
-Yes.

784
00:48:29,345 --> 00:48:31,430
Scram! Stop blocking the way!

785
00:48:31,514 --> 00:48:32,806
Gosh, we're leaving.

786
00:48:32,890 --> 00:48:35,601
Geez, I told them I was fine.

787
00:48:40,189 --> 00:48:44,360
Gosh, those sudden outbursts
must be what's keeping him so feisty.

788
00:48:44,443 --> 00:48:45,653
[box clatters]

789
00:48:48,656 --> 00:48:51,033
-Mr. Park!
-Oh, no! Mr. Park!

790
00:48:51,116 --> 00:48:53,702
Mr. Park! Oh heavens, what do we do?

791
00:48:53,786 --> 00:48:55,663
Goodness, Mr. Park.

792
00:48:55,746 --> 00:48:57,248
I'll administer CPR.

793
00:48:58,082 --> 00:48:59,542
-Please measure the time.
-Oh, no.

794
00:48:59,625 --> 00:49:00,626
Right.

795
00:49:06,215 --> 00:49:08,801
Yes, this is Pyeondongdo.

796
00:49:09,760 --> 00:49:11,428
The chopper will be arriving soon.

797
00:49:12,513 --> 00:49:14,932
Goodness, Mr. Park.

798
00:49:23,399 --> 00:49:24,608
[helicopter whirring]

799
00:49:29,905 --> 00:49:31,949
MEDICAL HELICOPTER

800
00:49:49,341 --> 00:49:52,177
The patient is a 65-year-old man.
He came in about 30 minutes ago,

801
00:49:52,261 --> 00:49:54,888
thinking it was indigestion,
complaining of chest pain.

802
00:49:54,972 --> 00:49:58,767
I administered NTG. He refused to visit
a hospital and collapsed within an hour.

803
00:49:58,851 --> 00:50:01,770
He was in a state of stupor
with no pulse, so I administered CPR.

804
00:50:01,854 --> 00:50:04,231
And we got ROSC within five minutes.

805
00:50:04,315 --> 00:50:05,899
Are you a doctor?

806
00:50:05,983 --> 00:50:07,693
Sorry? Oh, yes.

807
00:50:08,277 --> 00:50:10,529
Then come with us. Get in.

808
00:50:10,613 --> 00:50:12,281
-Come on.
-Go.

809
00:50:12,364 --> 00:50:14,658
-Go!
-We should hurry! We'll be late!

810
00:51:02,539 --> 00:51:04,750
ASONG HOSPITAL
STYLE
::cue()

811
00:51:09,254 --> 00:51:12,299
Ventricular wall motion is poor.
We'll have to do an emergency CAG.

812
00:51:12,383 --> 00:51:13,384
Yes, understood.

813
00:51:13,467 --> 00:51:14,968
CAG: CORONARY ANGIOGRAPHY

814
00:51:15,052 --> 00:51:17,554
RESTRICTED AREA

815
00:51:20,516 --> 00:51:21,975
INTENSIVE CARE UNIT

816
00:51:22,059 --> 00:51:23,769
-[Jiui sighs]
-[paramedic sighs]

817
00:51:23,852 --> 00:51:26,313
-Thank you for a job well done.
-Thank you.

818
00:51:26,397 --> 00:51:27,398
Take care.

819
00:51:28,232 --> 00:51:30,401
-Sir, just a moment.
-Yes?

820
00:51:31,443 --> 00:51:33,195
-What about me?
-Huh?

821
00:51:33,278 --> 00:51:34,363
-Huh?
-What do you mean?

822
00:51:34,446 --> 00:51:36,073
How do I get back?

823
00:51:36,156 --> 00:51:38,367
You? Why are you asking me that?

824
00:51:38,450 --> 00:51:40,411
I guess you could ask your health center.

825
00:51:40,953 --> 00:51:42,246
I'm leaving now.

826
00:51:42,329 --> 00:51:43,539
-Bye.
-Okay.

827
00:51:43,622 --> 00:51:45,082
Safe travels.

828
00:51:46,417 --> 00:51:49,336
Yes, situation room.
Yeopoong One has finished transferring…

829
00:51:49,420 --> 00:51:52,840
So we're just supposed to
find our own way back home, huh?

830
00:51:55,175 --> 00:51:57,386
Then why the hell
did he tell me to come? Damn it.

831
00:52:00,222 --> 00:52:01,640
How am I supposed to get back?

832
00:52:02,307 --> 00:52:06,979
[Ms. Hwang] The last ferry's already gone
for the day, so find a motel, sleep there,

833
00:52:07,062 --> 00:52:09,481
and take the first ferry back tomorrow.

834
00:52:09,565 --> 00:52:10,733
Oh, a ferry?

835
00:52:10,816 --> 00:52:13,152
[Ms. Hwang] Of course, a ferry.
What else would you take? A train?

836
00:52:13,235 --> 00:52:14,987
Never mind. Yes, I understand.

837
00:52:15,487 --> 00:52:16,739
[Ms. Hwang] Good work today.

838
00:52:16,822 --> 00:52:17,865
[hangs up]

839
00:52:19,491 --> 00:52:20,492
That's it?

840
00:52:22,578 --> 00:52:23,579
Oh, come on.

841
00:52:24,955 --> 00:52:25,956
[sighs]

842
00:52:28,500 --> 00:52:29,501
Man, I'm so exhausted.

843
00:52:31,128 --> 00:52:32,129
I'm starving.

844
00:52:33,756 --> 00:52:35,758
[♪ muffled pop music playing]

845
00:52:41,513 --> 00:52:42,848
[exhales deeply]

846
00:52:46,185 --> 00:52:49,104
Man, to think this is
my first meal in 24 hours…

847
00:52:51,440 --> 00:52:52,483
[sighs]

848
00:53:01,366 --> 00:53:03,327
[phone chimes]

849
00:53:05,996 --> 00:53:08,749
[chiming continues]

850
00:53:11,960 --> 00:53:14,379
Clap, clap, clap, welcome to hell.

851
00:53:14,463 --> 00:53:15,798
You won a ticket to hell!

852
00:53:15,881 --> 00:53:17,800
Pyeondongdo of all places?

853
00:53:17,883 --> 00:53:20,260
Hang on for a year,
then make a run for the mainland.

854
00:53:20,344 --> 00:53:22,721
If you just got here,
does that mean you have 340 days

855
00:53:22,805 --> 00:53:25,808
until you're allowed to transfer
to a different province? [cackles]

856
00:53:25,891 --> 00:53:28,435
[Jiui] "If you just got here,
does that mean you have 340 days?"

857
00:53:28,519 --> 00:53:29,978
Is this guy mocking me right now?

858
00:53:30,062 --> 00:53:32,815
It's because you were
a traitor to the nation in your past life.

859
00:53:32,898 --> 00:53:36,026
I was a helmsman on the turtle ship!
So why'd I get sent to an island?

860
00:53:36,109 --> 00:53:39,822
Come on, 340 days will go by
in the blink of an eye.

861
00:53:39,905 --> 00:53:42,282
The only downside is that
you don't get to go on leave. [chuckles]

862
00:53:42,366 --> 00:53:45,160
Man, these people are making me
lose my appetite.

863
00:53:48,121 --> 00:53:49,122
[sighs]

864
00:53:49,206 --> 00:53:51,208
[♪ muffled pop music continues playing]

865
00:54:00,050 --> 00:54:01,051
[groans]

866
00:54:02,427 --> 00:54:03,554
[grunts]

867
00:54:06,682 --> 00:54:09,685
I'm so tired…

868
00:54:09,768 --> 00:54:11,770
[♪ lullaby music playing]

869
00:54:15,816 --> 00:54:18,443
I should eat before I sleep.
I'm really hungry…

870
00:54:20,445 --> 00:54:22,364
That ramyeon is going to taste so good.

871
00:54:29,663 --> 00:54:32,374
-[motorcycle engine whirring]
-[cell phone ringing]

872
00:54:34,167 --> 00:54:35,168
[exclaims]

873
00:54:40,424 --> 00:54:41,425
[grunts]

874
00:54:43,760 --> 00:54:45,512
Hello? [groans]

875
00:54:46,179 --> 00:54:47,889
[Ms. Hwang]
Doctor, why aren't you here yet?

876
00:54:50,809 --> 00:54:52,060
I'm still at the…

877
00:54:52,144 --> 00:54:53,979
Why are you still on the mainland?

878
00:54:54,062 --> 00:54:56,106
You should've taken the first ferry back!

879
00:54:56,189 --> 00:55:00,444
Do you have any idea how busy it gets
at a public health center?

880
00:55:00,527 --> 00:55:02,529
It's because of the emergency--

881
00:55:02,613 --> 00:55:04,781
That was yesterday, not today!

882
00:55:04,865 --> 00:55:07,117
Hurry back
or you'll be reported for desertion.

883
00:55:07,200 --> 00:55:08,910
One warning for abandoning your post.

884
00:55:08,994 --> 00:55:10,120
Two warnings

885
00:55:10,203 --> 00:55:12,831
and you're barred
from transferring provinces.

886
00:55:12,914 --> 00:55:15,000
You wanna get tied down here
for three years, huh?

887
00:55:15,083 --> 00:55:19,046
[stammers] I'm going!
I'll get going right now.

888
00:55:19,880 --> 00:55:22,299
Oh, for crying out loud.
STYLE
::cue()

889
00:55:26,762 --> 00:55:29,681
-[seagulls squawking]
-[ship horn blares]

890
00:55:36,355 --> 00:55:39,566
YEOPOONG MARINE TRANSPORT

891
00:55:40,359 --> 00:55:41,360
[sighs]

892
00:55:42,819 --> 00:55:43,820
Ah.

893
00:55:50,285 --> 00:55:51,745
[line ringing]

894
00:55:53,914 --> 00:55:56,083
You told me that I could ask you for help

895
00:55:56,166 --> 00:55:59,920
if I was having any trouble
with something.

896
00:56:00,420 --> 00:56:02,005
It's about Pyeondongdo.

897
00:56:02,089 --> 00:56:04,841
Is there any other way to get there
that's not by ferry?

898
00:56:04,925 --> 00:56:07,386
I'd be okay with
a chopper or something too.

899
00:56:07,469 --> 00:56:10,389
[Ms. Hwang] Stop talking nonsense
and get your tail over here.

900
00:56:10,472 --> 00:56:12,974
And from now on,
if you're having trouble with anything,

901
00:56:13,058 --> 00:56:15,519
don't tell me about it
and just take care of it yourself.

902
00:56:15,602 --> 00:56:17,104
-I'm hanging up now!
-Hold on.

903
00:56:17,187 --> 00:56:18,605
-[line disconnects]
-Hello? Ms. Hwang…

904
00:56:20,023 --> 00:56:21,358
Are you kidding me?

905
00:56:21,441 --> 00:56:24,111
[announcer on PA]
The ship bound for Pyeondongdo

906
00:56:24,194 --> 00:56:25,612
is now departing.

907
00:56:26,780 --> 00:56:31,076
All remaining passengers,
please board the ship at this time.

908
00:56:39,584 --> 00:56:41,586
[♪ ethereal music plays]

909
00:57:28,550 --> 00:57:30,302
[♪ ethereal music fades]

910
00:57:30,385 --> 00:57:32,387
[♪ serene music playing]
STYLE
::cue()

911
00:58:04,252 --> 00:58:08,673
[Jiui] The three things one must avoid
encountering on an island.

912
00:58:13,011 --> 00:58:15,388
-Incidents…
-Please wake up.

913
00:58:15,472 --> 00:58:16,932
Move!

914
00:58:17,474 --> 00:58:18,475
[dog barks]

915
00:58:23,939 --> 00:58:24,940
People…

916
00:58:32,948 --> 00:58:34,199
All done.

917
00:58:39,579 --> 00:58:40,580
And…

918
00:58:47,879 --> 00:58:49,881
[♪ serene music continues]

919
00:59:20,871 --> 00:59:25,166
THE THREE THINGS ONE MUST AVOID
ENCOUNTERING ON AN ISLAND

920
00:59:25,250 --> 00:59:27,168
INCIDENTS,

921
00:59:27,252 --> 00:59:29,671
PEOPLE,

922
00:59:29,754 --> 00:59:32,299
AND…

923
00:59:45,395 --> 00:59:48,315
"SUN, PLEASE COME OUT
OF THE CLOUDS"

924
01:00:00,410 --> 01:00:03,330
DOCTOR ON THE EDGE

925
01:00:03,413 --> 01:00:05,790
[Hari] I mean, why do we keep
running into each other?

926
01:00:05,874 --> 01:00:08,001
[Jiui] Just be on your way
and stop crossing the line.

927
01:00:08,084 --> 01:00:09,753
Look at me. I almost crossed the line.

928
01:00:09,836 --> 01:00:11,296
Hey!

929
01:00:13,506 --> 01:00:14,841
Do you really not remember me?

930
01:00:16,217 --> 01:00:18,803
[Ms. Hwang] He actually went to
the county office to file a complaint.

931
01:00:18,887 --> 01:00:20,889
[Jeongbae] Come over here
if you've got a death wish.

932
01:00:21,473 --> 01:00:23,934
[Hari] Why get the surgery
if you're going to act like this?

933
01:00:24,017 --> 01:00:26,478
I'm scared! Come on.

934
01:00:26,561 --> 01:00:28,146
Are we expecting someone?

935
01:00:33,652 --> 01:00:35,654
Subtitle translation by: Yoon Hyuk Park
